{
  "texts": [
    "The yielded importance weightings subsequently multiply with respective feature maps.",
    "A summation operation followed by a ReLU activation function is performed on these weighted results to produce the Grad-CAM heatmaps.",
    "These localization maps indicate feature significance to class prediction using different colour schemes with deep red indicating the most significant/relevant characteristics and deep blue as the least influential factors for categorization.",
    "Therefore, such class-discriminative heatmaps are used in this research to visualize which image regions have the most influence to synthetic/original video classification.",
    "In comparison with class activation mapping (CAM), the Grad-CAM method can be applied to any CNN architectures even without re-training [86]."
  ]
}